sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant C as Client (Gerente)
    participant EC as ExportController
    participant ES as ExportService
    participant ER as ExportRepository
    participant DB as Database

    Note over C,DB: 1 · Exportação de turnos CSV — RF047 · RN26

    C->>+EC: GET /export/events/eventId/shifts
    Note over EC: requireAuth — JWT obrigatório
    EC->>+ES: exportShifts(eventId)
    ES->>+ER: getShiftsForExport(eventId)
    ER->>+DB: SELECT shifts JOIN athletes JOIN teams JOIN treadmills<br/>WHERE event_id = $1 ORDER BY started_at
    DB-->>-ER: shift rows[]
    ER-->>-ES: shifts[]
    ES->>ES: serializeCSV(shifts) → "id,athlete,team,treadmill,started_at,finished_at,km,speed\n..."
    ES-->>-EC: csvString
    EC-->>-C: 200 Content-Type: text/csv — shifts-eventId.csv

    Note over C,DB: 2 · Exportação de checkpoints CSV — RF048 · RN26

    C->>+EC: GET /export/events/eventId/checkpoints
    EC->>+ES: exportCheckpoints(eventId)
    ES->>+ER: getCheckpointsForExport(eventId)
    ER->>+DB: SELECT checkpoints JOIN shifts JOIN athletes<br/>WHERE shifts.event_id = $1 ORDER BY timestamp
    DB-->>-ER: checkpoint rows[]
    ER-->>-ES: checkpoints[]
    ES->>ES: serializeCSV(checkpoints) → "id,shift_id,athlete,type,distance,timestamp,sync_id\n..."
    ES-->>-EC: csvString
    EC-->>-C: 200 Content-Type: text/csv — checkpoints-eventId.csv

    Note over C,DB: 3 · Evento sem dados registrados

    C->>+EC: GET /export/events/eventId/shifts — evento sem dados
    EC->>+ES: exportShifts(999)
    ES->>+ER: getShiftsForExport(999)
    ER->>+DB: SELECT ... WHERE event_id = 999
    DB-->>-ER: []
    ER-->>-ES: []
    ES->>ES: serializeCSV([]) → header only
    ES-->>-EC: "id,athlete,team,...\n"
    EC-->>-C: 200 Content-Type: text/csv (arquivo só com cabeçalho)
